---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import DocsSidebar from "../../components/DocsSidebar.astro";
import AgentInstall from "../../components/AgentInstall.tsx";
---
<Layout
	title="Quickstart · flipagent docs"
	description="Three real flipagent examples you can run in two minutes — browse categories, find ending auctions, evaluate a listing."
>
	<div class="cmw cmw-bordered">
		<div class="docs-shell">
			<DocsSidebar />
			<article class="docs-content">
				<h1>Let's try it</h1>
				<p class="lead">Three small examples, each one a real flipagent flow. Pick the one that sounds useful and follow it through.</p>

				<h2 id="mcp">Take the MCP path</h2>
				<p>One command writes the MCP entry into your AI client's config, or paste the JSON yourself:</p>
				<AgentInstall client:visible />
				<p style="font-size:13.5px;">No key? <a href="/signup/">Grab one</a>.</p>

				<h2 id="playground">Or use the playground</h2>
				<p>Open <a href="/dashboard/?view=agent">the dashboard</a> in your browser — each example below has a button that opens it with the question pre-filled. Nothing to install.</p>

				<h2>Pick what to try</h2>
				<div class="features" style="margin:18px 0 8px;">
					<a class="feature" href="#categories">
						<div class="ic">Example 1</div>
						<h3>Browse categories</h3>
						<p>See what's available on eBay. Walk the category tree from the top.</p>
					</a>
					<a class="feature" href="#auctions">
						<div class="ic">Example 2</div>
						<h3>Find ending auctions</h3>
						<p>Pull the auctions about to close in a category. Time-window sourcing.</p>
					</a>
					<a class="feature" href="#evaluate">
						<div class="ic">Example 3</div>
						<h3>Evaluate one listing</h3>
						<p>Paste an eBay URL. Get back estimated profit, fees, and a buy/skip call.</p>
					</a>
				</div>

				<h2 id="categories">1. Browse categories</h2>
				<p>Ask:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>Show me the top-level eBay categories I can use for sourcing.</code></pre></div>
				<p style="margin-top:14px;">
					<a class="btn heat" href="/dashboard/?view=agent&seed=Show%20me%20the%20top-level%20eBay%20categories%20I%20can%20use%20for%20sourcing.">
						Open in playground
					</a>
				</p>

				<div class="docs-reply" style="margin-top:18px;">
					<div class="docs-reply-head">Agent reply</div>
					<div class="docs-reply-body">
						<p>Here are the top-level eBay categories. 34 roots in total. Drill in with <code>parentId</code> to reach listable leaves.</p>
						<table>
							<thead><tr><th>ID</th><th>Category</th></tr></thead>
							<tbody>
								<tr><td>220</td><td>Toys & Hobbies</td></tr>
								<tr><td>625</td><td>Cameras & Photo</td></tr>
								<tr><td>888</td><td>Sporting Goods</td></tr>
								<tr><td>1249</td><td>Video Games & Consoles</td></tr>
								<tr><td>11450</td><td>Clothing, Shoes & Accessories</td></tr>
								<tr><td>15032</td><td>Cell Phones & Accessories</td></tr>
								<tr><td>58058</td><td>Computers/Tablets & Networking</td></tr>
								<tr><td>64482</td><td>Sports Mem, Cards & Fan Shop</td></tr>
							</tbody>
						</table>
						<p style="color:var(--text-3); font-size:13px;">…and 26 more. Want me to drill into one?</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p style="font-size:13.5px; color:var(--text-3);">Called <code>flipagent_list_categories(&#123;&#125;)</code> with no args. Pass <code>parentId</code> to walk down a level.</p>

				<h2 id="auctions">2. Find ending auctions</h2>
				<p>Ask:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>Find game console auctions ending in the next 10 minutes.</code></pre></div>
				<p style="margin-top:14px;">
					<a class="btn heat" href="/dashboard/?view=agent&seed=Find%20game%20console%20auctions%20ending%20in%20the%20next%2010%20minutes.">
						Open in playground
					</a>
				</p>

				<div class="docs-reply" style="margin-top:18px;">
					<div class="docs-reply-head">Agent reply</div>
					<div class="docs-reply-body">
						<p>13 console auctions closing in the next 10 minutes. Sorted by ending time:</p>
						<table>
							<thead><tr><th>Ends (UTC)</th><th>Bid</th><th>Title</th></tr></thead>
							<tbody>
								<tr><td>17:16</td><td>$146.50</td><td>Nintendo 64 + Goldeneye, Tetris, cables</td></tr>
								<tr><td>17:17</td><td>$76.00</td><td>Game Boy Advance SP Silver AGS-001</td></tr>
								<tr><td>17:19</td><td>$800.00</td><td>Xbox Series X 1TB + controllers</td></tr>
								<tr><td>17:21</td><td>$36.00</td><td>PS1 SCPH-9001 + 4 games + memory cards</td></tr>
								<tr><td>17:21</td><td>$201.50</td><td>GameCube + 4 controllers, AV/component</td></tr>
								<tr><td>17:24</td><td>$300.00</td><td>3DS XL Galaxy Edition Purple</td></tr>
							</tbody>
						</table>
						<p>The PS1 bundle at $36 and N64 + games at $146.50 look soft. Want me to evaluate any of them for a profit estimate?</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p style="font-size:13.5px; color:var(--text-3);">Called <code>flipagent_search_items(&#123;q: "game console", buyingOption: "auction", sort: "ending_soonest", limit: 50&#125;)</code>.</p>

				<h2 id="evaluate">3. Evaluate one listing</h2>
				<p>Ask:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>Is https://www.ebay.com/itm/377151909505 worth flipping?</code></pre></div>
				<p style="margin-top:14px;">
					<a class="btn heat" href="/dashboard/?view=agent&seed=Is%20https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2F377151909505%20worth%20flipping%3F">
						Open in playground
					</a>
				</p>

				<div class="docs-reply" style="margin-top:18px;">
					<div class="docs-reply-head">Agent reply</div>
					<div class="docs-reply-body">
						<p><strong>Canon EF 50mm f/1.8 STM Lens</strong> · listed at <strong>$89.95</strong> · Used</p>
						<table>
							<thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead>
							<tbody>
								<tr><td>Sold p50 (30d, n=40)</td><td>$89.97</td></tr>
								<tr><td>Sales velocity</td><td>1.35 / day</td></tr>
								<tr><td>eBay fees + ship out</td><td>$12.75 + $10.00</td></tr>
								<tr><td>Bid ceiling (break-even)</td><td>$71.24</td></tr>
								<tr><td>Expected net at $89.95</td><td>−$22.53</td></tr>
							</tbody>
						</table>
						<p><strong>Verdict: skip.</strong> Median sold price is essentially the asking price, and ~$23 of fees and shipping kill the spread. The math only works at ≤$71 landed. Best Offer is enabled — anchor any offer at $71 or walk.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p style="font-size:13.5px; color:var(--text-3);">Called <code>flipagent_evaluate_item(&#123;itemId: "377151909505"&#125;)</code>. The job ran server-side; the agent polled <code>flipagent_get_evaluate_job</code> until it was done.</p>

				<h2>Where next</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Place the bid your agent picked → <a href="/docs/extension/">Chrome extension</a></li>
					<li>All the tools and endpoints → <a href="/docs/mcp/">MCP</a> · <a href="/docs/api/">API reference</a></li>
				</ul>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
